node.text:
"You guys...it worked! It actually worked! I’m still in absolute shock. Kevin hasn’t stopped smiling since we found out and I’ve been in disbelief ever since. But we’re pregnant! Like legit pregnant. There’s a baby growing inside of me. A baby Kevin and I have prayed for and fought for every single day since our wedding day. That’s 1,672 days to be exact.
⁣
I’ve dreamed of this day for a long time and I honestly started losing hope that it would ever come. There are just no words to describe it. And although it’s incredibly exciting for us, my heart aches so much for those who haven’t had success yet. I know how much these posts can hurt because I’ve been on the receiving end of that hurt for over four years. So just know, you’re on my mind and I’m always rooting for you
🤰 @while_we.wait
 

.
#newbornbaby #pregnantbelly #pregnantlife #pregnancylife #babybelly #pregobelly #preggobelly #pregnancystyle #healthypregnancy #fitpregnancy #mommytobe #mumtobe #mummytobe

node.text:
We show compassion, grace, and admiration for pregnant tummies. And then we are no longer pregnant. Almost instinctively we start to loathe, resent, and question our postpartum tummies. ⁣
⁣
Where did all the compassion, grace, and admiration go?⁣
⁣
Because it’s still the same tummy. We’re still the same person. Then why do we choose to be so critical? ⁣
⁣
During my pregnancy my tummy worked hard to care for me and my baby. The least I can do during postpartum is work equally as hard to care for my tummy, as is.⁣ ——
.
📸: @shelbysaywhatblog 

#pregnantbellybump #motherhoodthroughinstagram #postpartumbody #pregnancyjourney #pregnancysession #pregnancyjourney_
